Preheat the oven to 400 degrees. Bring a large #pot of water to a boil with a 
large pinch of @salt{}. Toss the @butternut squash{12%ounce} on a #baking sheet{} 
with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Place in 
the oven for ~{20-25%minutes}, tossing, halfway through cooking, until golden 
brown.

Once the water is boiling, add the @black Thai rice{3/4%cup} and cook for 
~{35-40%minutes}, until tender. When the rice is finished cooking, drain, rinse, 
and set aside.

While the squash and rice cook, thinly slice the @scallions{2}(thinly sliced), 
keeping the whites and greens separate. Pick, then chop the @parsley{1/4%ounce} 
(picked then chopped). Roughly chop the @shelled pistachios{2%ounce}.

In a large #bowl, combine the @red wine vinegar{2%tablespoon}, 
@honey{1%ounce}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Whisk in a large drizzle of olive oil. 
Toss in the rice, squash, @arugula{2%ounce}, scallions, and parsley.

Serve the forbidden rice salad with a sprinkle of pistachios on top and enjoy!

> This Wintery black rice salad is hearty, delicious, and packs a major nutritional punch. A tangy honey vinaigrette pulls it all together.